# Copenhagen 3D — Civic Budget Visualization

## Project Overview

Interactive 3D map application for Copenhagen civic participation / participatory budgeting.
Citizens can browse, vote on, and propose community projects visualized on a 3D city map.
Built for the BloxHub hackathon — adapted from a Gliwice (Poland) prototype.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: Single-file SPA (`public/index.html`, ~1770 lines)
  - MapLibre GL JS v4.7.1 (3D map rendering, building extrusion, vector tiles)
  - Three.js v0.160.0 (3D model loading — GLTF/GLB/STL — on map + detail preview)
  - deck.gl (CDN, ColumnLayer for data visualization — partially integrated)
  - Pure CSS (no framework), design tokens in `:root`
  - No build step, no bundler — all inline in index.html
- **Backend**: Express.js v4 static file server (`server.js`, port 3001)
- **Data**: Static GeoJSON files in `public/data/` (district boundaries, Frederiksberg OSM)
- **Testing**: Playwright screenshot script (`screenshot.js`) — headless=false with Metal GPU
- **Map tiles**: OpenFreeMap positron style

## Architecture

### Single HTML file structure (public/index.html):
1. **Lines 1-584**: CSS — design tokens, sidebar, project cards, markers, popups, facility panel, map controls, loading screen
2. **Lines 586-667**: HTML — loading overlay, header bar, map container, sidebar with project list + add form, project detail panel, facility panel, map controls, stats bar
3. **Lines 668-1771**: JavaScript (all in one `<script>` block)
   - State: `COPENHAGEN` center coords, `projects[]`, `markers{}`, `placingMode`, `pendingLocation`
   - `MODEL_URLS` — CC0 3D model URLs from GitHub (tree, bridge, shelter, bench, amphitheater, statue, fox, truck, duck, lantern, garden, toycar)
   - `DEMO_PROJECTS` (8 real Copenhagen projects with votes, coords, categories, districts)
   - `CATEGORIES` — playground, green, sport, culture, infra, other
   - `FACILITY_TYPES` — gym, workout, playground_city, skatepark, pitch, dog_park, harbour_bath
   - `CITY_FACILITIES` — 66 real Copenhagen outdoor facilities with coordinates
   - `DISTRICTS` — 10 Copenhagen districts with approximate polygon boundaries
   - Map initialization with pastel cartoon city styling (custom building colors, 3D trees, park bushes)
   - District boundary layer with click-to-highlight interaction
   - Project markers (quest-style "!" icons), voting system, project detail view with 3D model preview
   - Facility markers with filter toggles
   - Map view controls (pitch, bearing, opacity, building scale)
   - "Propose new project" flow — click-to-place with model upload

### Key data flow:
- Projects are stored in-memory array (`projects[]`) — no persistence
- Votes stored per-project in `voters[]` array (client-side only)
- 3D models loaded via Three.js GLTFLoader/STLLoader, rendered as MapLibre custom layers
- District boundaries rendered as MapLibre GeoJSON source with fill/line/symbol layers

## Design System

- **Style**: Notion-inspired clean UI with pastel cartoon city map
- **Fonts**: DM Sans (UI), Source Serif 4 (headings), JetBrains Mono (numbers/stats)
- **Colors**: Defined in CSS `:root` variables — green (#00a67e), blue (#2f80ed), red (#e03e3e), orange (#d9730d), purple (#6940a5)
- **Building colors**: Pastel palette based on height hash (warm white, cyan, pink, sage, sand, blue, lavender)
- **Map**: Light warm gray background, soft blue water, pastel buildings with 3D extrusion

## File Structure

```
copenhagen-3d/
├── public/
│   ├── index.html          # Complete SPA (HTML + CSS + JS)
│   └── data/
│       ├── bydele-kk.geojson       # Copenhagen district boundaries (official)
│       └── frederiksberg-osm.geojson # Frederiksberg municipality from OSM
├── server.js               # Express static server (port 3001)
├── screenshot.js           # Playwright screenshot automation
├── package.json            # Dependencies: express, playwright
└── node_modules/
```

## Running the App

```bash
npm start           # Starts Express on http://localhost:3001
node screenshot.js  # Capture screenshots (requires server running)
```

## Key Implementation Details

### 3D Buildings
- Vector tile source from OpenFreeMap positron
- Buildings removed from flat layers, re-added as `fill-extrusion` with pastel colors
- Height multiplied by 1.3x for dramatic effect
- Roof cap layer (building-glow) at 1.31x height for visual depth
- 3D trees on parks (fill-extrusion from landcover wood/forest)
- 3D park bushes (fill-extrusion from landcover grass/meadow)

### District System
- 10 districts with approximate polygon boundaries (in JS, not GeoJSON)
- Click district → highlight with fill opacity change + border + label
- Click again to deactivate
- Popup shows project count + facility count for district

### Project System
- 8 demo projects with real Copenhagen data (Superkilen, Nordhavn Cycle Bridge, Enghaveparken, etc.)
- Categories: playground, green, sport, culture, infra, other
- Each project has: id, name, desc, category, cost (DKK), votes, lng/lat, district, status, edition
- Status values: Completed, Planned, In Progress, Concept
- 3D models loaded from CC0 GitHub repos

### Voting
- Client-side only (no backend persistence)
- Toggle vote on/off per project
- Vote count updates in real-time in sidebar, detail view, popup, and stats bar

### Project Placement
- "Propose new project" enters PLACING mode
- Click map to set location (crosshair cursor)
- Form: name, description, category, cost, 3D model upload (.glb/.gltf/.stl)
- New project added to in-memory array + map

### Model Controls (in detail view)
- Scale slider (0.1x - 5x)
- Rotation slider (0° - 360°)
- Move grid (NSEW + reset) — 5m steps
- All changes applied in real-time to map model layer

## Known Issues / TODO

- deck.gl integration started but not fully utilized
- No authentication or user system
- Playwright screenshots require headed mode with Metal GPU (`--use-gl=angle --use-angle=metal`)
- Multiple Three.js renderers share one GL context (standard MapLibre pattern, acceptable for this scale)

## Copenhagen-Specific Data

- Currency: DKK (Danish Krone)
- Districts: Indre By, Norrebro, Vesterbro, Osterbro, Christianshavn, Amager Vest, Amager Ost, Valby, Bispebjerg, Nordhavn
- Civic participation: Lokaludvalg (local councils), city budget proposals
- Source reference: kk.dk/politik/lokaludvalg (Copenhagen Municipality)

## Coding Conventions

- Communicate with the user in Polish
- Code, comments, and commit messages in English
- No build step — edit index.html directly
- Test changes by reloading browser at http://localhost:3001
- For screenshots: use Playwright with headed mode + Metal GPU flags
- Prefer minimal changes — this is a hackathon prototype
- Keep everything in the single index.html unless splitting becomes necessary
